expected_result: "Latest CLI/SDK/ecosystem are audited in isolated temp projects, concrete non-duplicate findings are fixed or documented, GitHub PR/issues/dependency/security reports are handled, release gates and observability checks pass, a PR is reviewed, green, and merged."
comments[9]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-02T21:59:44.429Z",codex-ecosystem-lane-20260602,"Ecosystem lane start: auditing external pm packages and isolated temp-project package-first dogfood with separate PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH; no claim/release and no repo file edits."
  "2026-06-02T21:59:49.442Z",codex-sdk-lane-20260602,"SDK/custom-item-fields lane start: auditing GitHub issue #97 / pm-qvdj for registerItemFields, create/update contracts/help, validation, tests, and SDK docs/examples. Scope is findings only; no claim/release and no code edits planned."
  "2026-06-02T21:59:54.061Z",codex-ci-lane-20260602,"Specialist CI/GitHub/dependency/security/observability lane start: inspecting GitHub PRs/issues/Dependabot/security access, workflow status, commander PR #93, dependency audit/outdated state, and Sentry/telemetry gate command contracts. No claim/release; no repo file edits."
  "2026-06-02T21:59:54.341Z",codex-extension-lane-20260602,"Audit lane start (codex-extension-lane-20260602): focused on extension service/renderer override diagnostics for GitHub issue #96 / pm-5teq. Scope: registerService/registerRenderer, extension doctor, activation metadata, warnings, docs, tests. No claim/release; findings-only unless tiny isolated doc/test typo."
  "2026-06-02T22:01:51.034Z",codex-ci-lane-20260602,"Specialist CI/GitHub/dependency/security/observability lane final: GitHub open surface is PR #93 plus issues #96/#97; PR #93 commander 15 has clean merge state and all CI checks passing. Recent latest-main CI/Docs/Dependabot/Nightly runs pass; older Auto Release 26804332718 and Release 26804564260 failed because the release reliability gate lacked required Sentry auth in Actions, while local Sentry gate with telemetry off reports 0 critical/high. Dependabot alerts returned all fixed; secret-scanning returned no alerts; code-scanning API returned no analysis. pnpm audit reports 0 vulnerabilities; pnpm outdated only reports commander 14.0.3 -> 15.0.0. Local health summary ok. No repo file edits by this lane. Follow-ups: merge/close PR #93 after commander 15 compatibility review, configure/verify release Sentry secret or rerun release, add code-scanning setup if desired, and fix current compile error in src/core/extensions/item-fields.ts before rerunning full gates."
  "2026-06-02T22:02:41.433Z",codex-extension-lane-20260602,"Extension override diagnostics lane final findings: GitHub #96 reproduces on current build in isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH after pm init. A single registerService('output_format', () => ({format:'toon'})) makes list-open --json and extension doctor --json output only {format:'toon'}; a single registerRenderer('json', ...) makes both output only the renderer payload. Exact code: registerService/registerRenderer append global overrides in src/core/extensions/loader.ts:1644 and :1661; output_format is exempted from service collision warnings in CHAINED_SERVICE_NAMES at loader.ts:2113; doctor only exposes counts/warnings in src/cli/commands/extension.ts:1488 and deep activation counts at :1582, so one unsafe override has activation_failure_count 0 and no warning. Runtime: src/core/output/output.ts:227 applies service override before renderer, :247 applies renderer; output warnings are not surfaced in normal output. Minimal recommendations: add activation/doctor warnings for globally scoped output_format service and toon/json renderer registrations (include extension layer/name, format/service, and command paths/absence); make extension doctor bypass output_format service/renderers or run with native rendering so diagnostics cannot be corrupted by the thing being diagnosed; document safe contracts in docs/EXTENSIONS.md and docs/SDK.md: output_format must return context.payload/null/undefined unless it owns the command, renderer must return null for unrelated payloads; update RendererOverride type/runtime if null fallback is intended. Tests: add unit coverage in extension-loader/extension-command for unsafe global output warnings and integration repro that doctor --json remains parseable. Verification: pnpm build passed before shared lane edits; focused tests were blocked later by unrelated TS error in src/core/extensions/item-fields.ts known_fields/PmCliErrorContext; pm health --check-only --summary --json passed."
  "2026-06-02T22:02:45.778Z",codex-sdk-lane-20260602,"SDK/custom-item-fields lane final: issue #97 is valid. Current tree now has a partial concurrent implementation (item-fields parser + commander --field contracts) but build is blocked by src/core/extensions/item-fields.ts using unsupported PmCliErrorContext.known_fields; create/update still need --field values wired into runCreate/runUpdate, changed_fields, tool/MCP contracts, docs, and focused tests. Commands: pnpm build passed before concurrent edit; isolated repro showed pm create --field => unknown_option; focused tests now fail at tsc before execution."
  "2026-06-02T22:06:17.511Z",codex-ecosystem-lane-20260602,"Ecosystem lane final: pnpm build passed; npm run dogfood:package-first passed in isolated temp PM_PATH=/tmp/pm-dogfood-Ei4ZcI/project/.agents/pm; npm search found 15 pm-cli/pm-package packages; all 15 installed/activated in separate temp projects with package doctor exit 0 and no activation/load failures. Only note: pm-slack emits PM_SLACK_WEBHOOK not set when credentialless."
  "2026-06-02T22:19:38.596Z",codex-broad-audit-20260602,"Evidence so far: commander 15 incorporated from PR #93; strict Sentry gate passed after expected structural validation CommandErrors were classified; telemetry stack healthy with queue depth 0 and recent events; release gates passed sequentially (2103 tests, 100% coverage, secret scan, npx smoke, package-first dogfood, npm pack dry-run, compatibility); external package lane installed and doctored 15 current npm packages successfully."
